This brings us to two new formulae. <<<
% here we use a block-level annotation to set the display mode to "inline", which renders all formulae in the block in a single line
#[inline, default]

f : N x N -> Z
f(a, b) := c
where c := a - b

g : N x N -> Z
g(a, b) := d
where d := a + b
>>> With these, we can define another one:
<<<
% a hidden formula is not shown in the LaTeX output, but is still available for use in other formulae
@[hidden]
abs : Z -> N
abs(x) := {
    0 - x if x < 0
    x otherwise
}

% now this formula can use the hidden one
h : N x N -> N
h(a, b) := e * 2
where e := abs(f(a, b) * g(a, b))
>>>